[1]
Date: Fri 9 Mar 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Official web site of Rospotrebnadzor [trans. Corr.AS, edited]
<http://www.rospotrebnadzor.ru/sanepid/glps>

Hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome in Lipetsk, Voronej, Tambov and
Ryazan regions
-----------------------------------------------
As of 9 Mar 2007, 585 cases of hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome
(HFRS) have been registered in 4 districts of the Central Federal
Region of the Russian Federation. These comprise 243 cases in the
Lipetsk region, 197 cases in the Voronej region, 75 in the Tambov
region and 70 cases in the Ryazan region.
The increase in morbidity ceased in the Voronej and Lipetsk regions
during the period from December 2006 to February 2007. There have
been no new cases registered in the Voronej region since 15 Feb 2007
or in the Lipetsk region since 23 Feb 2007.
(1) The Office of Rospotrebnadzor has supplied the following
statistics for HFRS cases in the Tambov region for the period up to 9
Mar 2007: A total of 75 cases were registered in 16 districts, 41
settlements and in the cities of Tambov, Michurinsk, Kotovsk, and
Jerdevke. During the past 10 days, 4 new cases have been registered.
In 63 out of the 75 cases (84 percent), the diagnosis was confirmed
by laboratory tests. As of 9 Mar 2007, 63 patients are still in
hospital. The majority of patients were of working age; 32 percent
were unemployed, 22.7 percent were pensioners, 22.7 percent were
workers, 7 percent were students and school children, and 2.7 percent
pre-school children.
The most recent 5 cases were registered in the Nikiforovskoe district
on 16 Feb, in the Pichaevskiy district on 18 Feb, and in the
Bondarskoy district on 18 & 23 Feb 2007 and on 3 Mar 2007. Thus,
during the past 26 days, only 5 cases of HFRS have been registered.
(2) 70 cases of HFRS in the Ryazan region have been recorded in 16
districts, 35 settlements and the city of Ryazan. All the cases were
hospitalized. Laboratory confirmed cases comprised 74 percent (52).
By 9 Mar 2007, only 4 patients were still in the hospital, and 52 had
been discharged. One patient died. In 14 cases, the initial diagnosis
was not confirmed. In 2 cases (2.9 percent), the disease was severe;
in 57 cases, moderate (74.3 percent); and in 11 cases, mild (15.7
percent). There were no under 14-year-old children among the
patients. In total, 64.3 percent (45 persons) of HFRS patients were
men, 35.7 percent (25 persons) were women. The distribution of
patients by profession and social status is as follows: workers -
31.4 percent (22.5 percent in agricultural employment), pensioners -
21.4 percent (15), unemployed - 20 percent (14), servants - 8.7
percent (6), students - 2.9 percent (2), foresters and hunters - 4.3
percent (3), physically disabled persons - 5.7 percent (4), other -
5.7 percent (4). The last 3 cases were registered on 23 & 26 Feb 2007
and on 6 Mar 2007. Thus, during the past 16 days, only 3 cases of
HFRS have been registered.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[According to the detailed report of the Rospotrebnadzor Office, the
epidemic situation for HFRS in the Central Federal Region of Russia
is nearly normal. There have been no new cases in the Voronej and
Lipetsk regions since the end of February 2007. Four new cases have
been registered in the Tambov region during the last 10 days, and 3
new cases in the Ryazan during the last 16 days.
All these 4 regions: Lipetsk, Voronej, Tambov and Ryazan belong to
Central Federal District (Okrug). In total, 18 regions form the
Central Federal District (Okrug). They are Belgorod, Bryansk,
Voronezh, Vladimir, Ivanovo, Kaluga, Kostrima, Kursk, Lipetsk, Orel,
Ryasan, Smolensk, Tambov, Tver, Tula, Yaroslav, Moscow regions and
Moscow city. - Mod.NP]
